+ Apache Hive\nQuery Lifecycle
++ Step 1: Submission
+++_ User / service sends query
+++_ Cluster / SQL endpoint
++ Step 2: Access Check
+++_ Table ACLs evaluated
++ Step 3: Location Lookup
+++_ Hive metastore queried
+++_ Table metadata retrieved
++ Step 4: Path Returned
+++_ Storage URI returned
+++_ e.g. abfss://...
++ Step 5: Data Request
+++_ Authenticate to storage
+++_ SP, passthrough, instance profile
++ Step 6: Data Returned
+++_ Storage sends raw data
++ Step 7: Policy Enforcement
+++_ Cluster applies last-mile filtering
++ Step 8: Result Delivery
+++_ Result back to principal
-- Differences vs UC
---_ No centralized fine-grained governance
---_ Manual service accounts & secrets
---_ Mount points or passthrough needed
---_ Less integrated audit logging
@endmindmap
